# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Workspace-root .gitignore for a lesson-builder workspace.
# Copy this to `<workspace_root>/.gitignore` at bootstrap time, then adapt the
# course-carve-out section at the bottom for your actual course codes.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Dependencies
node_modules/
package-lock.json

# Local env (holds VITE_DESMOS_KEY and similar per-developer secrets)
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local

# Build output / cache
dist/
.vite/
__pycache__/
*.pyc

# Server runtime artifacts
**/server/.isolated/
**/server/.uploads/
**/server/.proxy-port
**/server/chat.log

# Lesson-builder scratch (Phase 3 specialist outputs before splice assembly)
**/.build-scratch/

# Course materials (copyrighted lectures, textbooks, private notes)
**/course_materials/
**/materials/
**/source/
**/notes/

# LaTeX / PDFs (re-allowed selectively below per course)
*.pdf
*.tex
*.aux
*.synctex.gz
*.fdb_latexmk
*.fls

# Claude Code settings
.claude/

# OS files
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Generated media / screenshots
media/
screenshots/
chat_*.png

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Course-level carve-outs.
#
# Pattern: ignore the whole course directory except its `claude_lessons/` tree,
# then re-allow specific tracked reference artifacts (formula sheets, guides).
# Duplicate and adapt per course in the workspace.
#
# Example for a course "<COURSE_DIR>":
#
#   <COURSE_DIR>/*
#   !<COURSE_DIR>/claude_lessons/
#   !<COURSE_DIR>/<COURSE_DIR>_formula_sheet.pdf
#   !<COURSE_DIR>/<COURSE_DIR>_formula_sheet.tex
#
# Replace <COURSE_DIR> with the actual directory name (e.g. `MATH101`).
# Without the explicit `!…pdf` re-allow, the `*.pdf` rule above would drop it.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
